The paper discusses a new family of Intensional RDBs (IRDBs) that extend traditional RDBs with Big Data and flexible schema features. The paper focuses on the interoperability features of IRDBs and how they can be queried using standard SQL. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
